========================================================================
det(I+2A) RECURRENCE ANALYSIS
========================================================================

--- Part 1: I+2A = J+S Decomposition ---
For tournament T with adjacency A (A_{ij} = 1 if i→j):
  A + A^T = J - I  (all pairs have exactly one arc)
  S = A - A^T  (skew-symmetric)
  2A = (J-I) + S
  I + 2A = J + S

So det(I+2A) = det(J+S) where:
  J = all-ones matrix (rank 1, eigenvalue n with eigenvector 1)
  S = skew-symmetric (eigenvalues purely imaginary)

--- Part 2: How det(I+2A) changes under vertex deletion ---

